shapes

Class TriangularPrism

  • java.lang.Object
    • shapes.TriangularPrism

  • public class TriangularPrism
extends java.lang.Object

    Contains triangular prism attributes and algorithms to modify the attributes.

    Triangular prism - a polyhedron made of a triangular base, a translated copy, and 3 faces joining corresponding sides.

    Since:
    1.0 (02/13/2017)
    Version:
    1.0.1 (01/08/2019)
    Author:
    Brady Lange - LinkedIn

    • Field Detail

      • area

        private double area
        The measurement of the surface.

        Formula:

        • (((base * depth) / 2.0) * 2) + (base * height) + (height * sideTwo) + (height * sideThree)

      • volume

        private double volume
        The amount of space that is occupied.

        Formula:

        • ((base * depth) / 2.0) * height

      • perimeter

        private double perimeter
        The measurement of the continuous line forming the boundary.

        Formula:

        • 2 * area + (base + sideTwo + sideThree) * height

      • base

        private double base
        The side which is perpendicular to the altitude.

      • height

        private double height
        The measurement from base to top.

      • depth

        private double depth
        The measurement from the top to the bottom.

      • sideTwo

        private double sideTwo
